The paper discusses learning algorithms for robots to solve real-world tasks, which suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO). The use of generative models and policy networks indicates a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the approach to ball-throwing in the presence of obstacles suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
